If the result overflows, return 0.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef reverse_integer(x: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `x` (int): A 32-bit signed integer.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the reversed integer if it does not overflow, otherwise returns 0.\\n\", \"code\": \"def reverse_integer(x: int) -> int:\\n    sign = -1 if x < 0 else 1\\n    x *= sign\\n    rev = 0\\n    while x:\\n        rev = rev * 10 + x % 10\\n        x //= 10\\n    return rev * sign\", \"tests\": [\"assert reverse_integer(123) == 321\", \"assert reverse_integer(-123) == -321\", \"assert reverse_integer(1534236469) == 0\", \"assert reverse_integer(-2147483648) == 0\"] }"
